# Skill Router

Use this rule when a request should be routed to the best available skill, project rule, or workflow before work begins.

## Routing Workflow

1. Identify the capabilities required: coding, debugging, testing, review, planning, UI/UX, visual design, prototype, docs, data, browser automation, deployment, GitHub/CI, security, Figma/design handoff, or mixed.
2. Respect explicitly named rules or skills first.
3. Inspect available rule/skill names and descriptions when needed.
4. Choose one primary workflow and at most two supporting workflows.
5. Do not load or apply every rule just because it exists.
6. If the right workflow is unavailable, proceed normally and state the assumption briefly.

## Capability Routing

Use capability matches before hard-coded names:

- Coding and implementation: code, implement, refactor, development.
- Test-first work: test-driven, TDD, unit tests, regression tests.
- Debugging: debug, bug, failing test, runtime error, broken behavior.
- Planning: plan, roadmap, milestones, decomposition.
- Verification: verify, QA, validation, completion.
- Review: review, PR comments, critique, risk scan.
- UI/UX: UI, UX, layout, accessibility, dashboard, component.
- Visual design: brand, visual, style, design system, banner.
- Prototypes: prototype, demo, animation, HTML prototype, motion.
- Figma/design handoff: Figma, node, design-to-code.
- Documents/data/slides: document, spreadsheet, presentation, deck.
- Browser automation: browser, screenshot, Playwright, web test.
- Deployment: deploy, hosting, Vercel, Netlify, Cloudflare, Render.
- GitHub/CI: GitHub, PR, Actions, CI, checks, gh.
- Security: security, threat model, best practices.
- Skill/plugin authoring: create skill, edit skill, plugin.

## Known Aliases

These are examples only, not requirements: `using-superpowers`, `test-driven-development`, `systematic-debugging`, `verification-before-completion`, `ui-ux-pro-max`, `huashu-design`, `karpathy-guidelines`, `gh-fix-ci`, `gh-address-comments`.

## Scoring

When several workflows match, choose by explicit user request, strongest metadata match, narrower specialist over broad generalist, package entry skill over sub-skill, then lower context cost.

## Communication

Before starting substantial work, state the selected capability/workflow in one short sentence. Then execute the task.

